exercises.statement:
In each of (a)-(e) prove that the specified subset H is a subgroup of the given group G:
(a) G = ℤ, H = nℤ for n ∈ ℤ⁺
(b) G = ℤ/20ℤ, H = ⟨4̄⟩
(c) G = S₃, H = {1, (1 2 3), (1 3 2)}
(d) G = D₈, H = {1, r², s, sr²}
(e) G = GL₂(ℝ), H = {A ∈ GL₂(ℝ) | det(A) = 1}

Show that the following subsets of ℤ are not subgroups:
(a) {n ∈ ℤ | n ≥ 0}
(b) {n ∈ ℤ | n is odd}
